    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-08-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Newport, R. I.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-08-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 10th instant stating that the Department has signified to the
                    chargé d’affaires <hi rend="italic">ad interim</hi> of Germany its cordial
                    concurrence in the appointment of Mr. Schmidt, late vice-consul of Germany at
                    Apia, as president of the municipal council in Samoa.</p>
                <p>I have informed Lord Rosebery by telegram of the fact, as well as of the
                    acceptance by Mr. Ide of the post of chief justice of Samoa, which you were good
                    enough to communicate to me in your note of the 6th instant.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
